      Constructors 
      Constructor Description
      time​(java.lang.Object... args)
      Class constructor.
      A time can be created in the following ways: A string with following format: "hh[:mm[:ss]]" A number representing elapsed milliseconds since midnight 2 or 3 numbers: hours (0 to 23), minutes (0 to 59) and optionally seconds (0 to 59, if absent 0 is used) Any other combination of values will produce an error.

        Class constructor.
        A time can be created in the following ways:
        • A string with following format: "hh[:mm[:ss]]"
        • A number representing elapsed milliseconds since midnight
        • 2 or 3 numbers: hours (0 to 23), minutes (0 to 59) and optionally seconds (0 to 59, if absent 0 is used)
        Any other combination of values will produce an error.
